Class DayOfWeek

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.BaseCount<DayOfWeek>
com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.DayOfWeek
All Implemented Interfaces:
Countable, NextValue<DayOfWeek>, Sized, MapFactory<Long,​DayOfWeek>, Arithmetic<DayOfWeek>, Castable, CastTrait, DoubleQuantizable, IntegerNumeric<DayOfWeek>, Maximizable<DayOfWeek>, Minimizable<DayOfWeek>, Quantizable, Stringable, StringSource, Source<Long>, Comparable<DayOfWeek>, Supplier<Long>
public class DayOfWeek extends BaseCount<DayOfWeek>
Typesafe value for day of week. The value stored in the BaseCount superclass is the ISO day of the week ordinal, where MONDAY is 0 and SUNDAY is 6. The Java day of the week (see java.time.DayOfWeek), where MONDAY is 1 and SUNDAY is 7 also supported.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo), matthieun
